  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated WASH support in response to the drought induced emergency in Aw-Bare, Gursum and T/Gulled Woredas of Fafan Zone</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fafan Zone is one of the areas which are severely affected by drought as the result of the current El Nino phenomenon. This has resulted in irregularities in rainfall patterns, shortage of food and water and emergency nutrition situation. 
The 2015 Joint Inter &#x2013; Agency Deyer needs assessment revealed that most of the woredas in Fafan have no well-planned preparedness and budget allocation for emergency response. The latrine and water supply coverage of the woredas in the zone were low and there were disease outbreaks in some woredas like kebribayah, Tuliguled and Gursum.  The top 5 causes of morbidity for under-5 years reported in the same period were pneumonia, diarrhoea, measles, malnutrition and upper respiratory tract Infections.
The overall objective of the project is to enhance the availability and utilization of Water, Sanitation and Hygiene services in Aw-Bare, Gursum and Tullliguled Woredas of Fafan Zone from April 11 to October  10, 2016. Hence, the project aims to address problems related to optimal hygiene and sanitation practices by raising the awareness of the community and creating an enabling environment. It will also enhance the availability of water by rehabilitation of the existing non-functional boreholes in the three woredas. The community&apos;s capacity to manage the water resources will be improved through establishment of 3 water and sanitation committee and training the established committee members. 
This project will be implemented with strong partnership with the local government line offices and the community. Coordination with other humanitarian actors will also be ensured through close collaboration, periodic discussions and brainstorming sessions.</narrative>
  </description>
